cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of deep neural networks for traffic prediction using time series data obtained by sensors mounted on road segments. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses a graph of a vehicular road network to infer the interaction between adjacent road segments, which involves the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and graph theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to capture the temporal dynamics of the traffic data, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
